metadata.name: FACT_DEX_TRADES
metadata.comment: Contains DEX and launchpad trading data, capturing swap events across different decentralized exchanges and launchpad platforms in the TON ecosystem.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: Timestamp of the block when the trade event occurred, converted from event_time.

EVENT_TYPE.name: EVENT_TYPE
EVENT_TYPE.comment: Type of the event: 'trade' for normal DEX swaps or 'launch' for when liquidity is collected from a bonding curve and sent to DEX.

PROJECT_TYPE.name: PROJECT_TYPE
PROJECT_TYPE.comment: Type of project: 'dex' for classical AMM DEXs or 'launchpad' for bonding curve launchpads.

PROJECT.name: PROJECT
PROJECT.comment: Name of the project (e.g., ston.fi, dedust.io, megaton.fi, tonco, ton.fun, gaspump).

POOL_ADDRESS.name: POOL_ADDRESS
POOL_ADDRESS.comment: Address of the pool where the trade occurred. Null if the pool is not known.

TRADER_ADDRESS.name: TRADER_ADDRESS
TRADER_ADDRESS.comment: Address of the trader who executed the swap.

TOKEN_BOUGHT_ADDRESS.name: TOKEN_BOUGHT_ADDRESS
TOKEN_BOUGHT_ADDRESS.comment: Address of the token that was bought. May include special wrapped TON aliases.

TOKEN_SOLD_ADDRESS.name: TOKEN_SOLD_ADDRESS
TOKEN_SOLD_ADDRESS.comment: Address of the token that was sold. May include special wrapped TON aliases.

AMOUNT_BOUGHT_RAW.name: AMOUNT_BOUGHT_RAW
AMOUNT_BOUGHT_RAW.comment: Raw amount of the token bought without dividing by 10^decimals. To get decimals, use the jetton_metadata table.

AMOUNT_SOLD_RAW.name: AMOUNT_SOLD_RAW
AMOUNT_SOLD_RAW.comment: Raw amount of the token sold without dividing by 10^decimals. To get decimals, use the jetton_metadata table.

ROUTER_ADDRESS.name: ROUTER_ADDRESS
ROUTER_ADDRESS.comment: Address of the router used for the trade. Null if the router is not used by the project.

VOLUME_TON.name: VOLUME_TON
VOLUME_TON.comment: Volume of the trade in TON. Calculated based on the amount of tokens traded if the trade involves TON, wrapped TON, USDT, USDC, or LSD (stTON, tsTON, hTON).

VOLUME_USD.name: VOLUME_USD
VOLUME_USD.comment: Volume of the trade in USD. Calculated based on the amount of tokens traded if the trade involves TON, wrapped TON, USDT, USDC, or LSD.

REFERRAL_ADDRESS.name: REFERRAL_ADDRESS
REFERRAL_ADDRESS.comment: Referral address if specified. Null if the referral is not specified or not supported by the project.

PLATFORM_TAG.name: PLATFORM_TAG
PLATFORM_TAG.comment: Platform address. Null if the platform is not specified or not supported by the project.

QUERY_ID.name: QUERY_ID
QUERY_ID.comment: Query ID of the transaction. Null if query ID is not supported by the project.

EVENT_TIME.name: EVENT_TIME
EVENT_TIME.comment: Unix timestamp when the trade event occurred.

FACT_DEX_TRADES_ID.name: FACT_DEX_TRADES_ID
FACT_DEX_TRADES_ID.comment: Unique identifier for the DEX trade record.

metadata.name: FACT_TRANSACTIONS
metadata.comment: Contains information about transactions in the TON blockchain, tracking account changes, fees, and computation results.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: Timestamp of the block when the transaction was processed, converted from now.

PREV_TX_HASH.name: PREV_TX_HASH
PREV_TX_HASH.comment: Hash of the previous transaction for the same account.

TX_SUCCEEDED.name: TX_SUCCEEDED
TX_SUCCEEDED.comment: Boolean flag indicating if the transaction succeeded. Set to FALSE if aborted is TRUE.

ABORTED.name: ABORTED
ABORTED.comment: Boolean flag indicating if the transaction was aborted.

ACCOUNT.name: ACCOUNT
ACCOUNT.comment: Account address associated with the transaction.

ORIG_STATUS.name: ORIG_STATUS
ORIG_STATUS.comment: Original status of the account before the transaction.

END_STATUS.name: END_STATUS
END_STATUS.comment: End status of the account after the transaction.

COMPUTE_SUCCESS.name: COMPUTE_SUCCESS
COMPUTE_SUCCESS.comment: Boolean flag indicating if the computation was successful.

COMPUTE_SKIPPED.name: COMPUTE_SKIPPED
COMPUTE_SKIPPED.comment: Boolean flag indicating if the computation was skipped.

ACTION_RESULT_CODE.name: ACTION_RESULT_CODE
ACTION_RESULT_CODE.comment: Result code for the action phase.

ACTION_SUCCESS.name: ACTION_SUCCESS
ACTION_SUCCESS.comment: Boolean flag indicating if the action phase was successful.

ACTION_SKIPPED_ACTIONS.name: ACTION_SKIPPED_ACTIONS
ACTION_SKIPPED_ACTIONS.comment: Number of actions that were skipped.

ACTION_VALID.name: ACTION_VALID
ACTION_VALID.comment: Boolean flag indicating if the action was valid.

ACTION_NO_FUNDS.name: ACTION_NO_FUNDS
ACTION_NO_FUNDS.comment: Boolean flag indicating if there were insufficient funds for the action.

ACTION_STATUS_CHANGE.name: ACTION_STATUS_CHANGE
ACTION_STATUS_CHANGE.comment: Status change during the action phase.

COMPUTE_MSG_STATE_USED.name: COMPUTE_MSG_STATE_USED
COMPUTE_MSG_STATE_USED.comment: Boolean flag indicating if the message state was used during computation.

DESCR.name: DESCR
DESCR.comment: Description or type of the transaction.

BLOCK_WORKCHAIN.name: BLOCK_WORKCHAIN
BLOCK_WORKCHAIN.comment: Workchain ID of the block containing this transaction.

BLOCK_SEQNO.name: BLOCK_SEQNO
BLOCK_SEQNO.comment: Sequence number of the block containing this transaction.

BLOCK_SHARD.name: BLOCK_SHARD
BLOCK_SHARD.comment: Shard ID of the block containing this transaction.

MC_BLOCK_SEQNO.name: MC_BLOCK_SEQNO
MC_BLOCK_SEQNO.comment: Masterchain block sequence number referenced by this transaction.

STORAGE_FEES_COLLECTED.name: STORAGE_FEES_COLLECTED
STORAGE_FEES_COLLECTED.comment: Storage fees collected during the transaction.

CREDIT_DUE_FEES_COLLECTED.name: CREDIT_DUE_FEES_COLLECTED
CREDIT_DUE_FEES_COLLECTED.comment: Credit fees collected during the transaction.

STORAGE_FEES_DUE.name: STORAGE_FEES_DUE
STORAGE_FEES_DUE.comment: Storage fees due for the transaction.

ACCOUNT_STATE_HASH_BEFORE.name: ACCOUNT_STATE_HASH_BEFORE
ACCOUNT_STATE_HASH_BEFORE.comment: Hash of the account state before the transaction.

ACCOUNT_STATE_HASH_AFTER.name: ACCOUNT_STATE_HASH_AFTER
ACCOUNT_STATE_HASH_AFTER.comment: Hash of the account state after the transaction.

ACCOUNT_STATE_CODE_HASH_BEFORE.name: ACCOUNT_STATE_CODE_HASH_BEFORE
ACCOUNT_STATE_CODE_HASH_BEFORE.comment: Hash of the account code before the transaction.

ACCOUNT_STATE_CODE_HASH_AFTER.name: ACCOUNT_STATE_CODE_HASH_AFTER
ACCOUNT_STATE_CODE_HASH_AFTER.comment: Hash of the account code after the transaction.

INSTALLED.name: INSTALLED
INSTALLED.comment: Boolean flag indicating if code was installed during the transaction.

DESTROYED.name: DESTROYED
DESTROYED.comment: Boolean flag indicating if the account was destroyed during the transaction.

IS_TOCK.name: IS_TOCK
IS_TOCK.comment: Boolean flag indicating if this is a tick-tock transaction.

CREDIT_FIRST.name: CREDIT_FIRST
CREDIT_FIRST.comment: Boolean flag indicating if credit was processed first.

COMPUTE_ACCOUNT_ACTIVATED.name: COMPUTE_ACCOUNT_ACTIVATED
COMPUTE_ACCOUNT_ACTIVATED.comment: Boolean flag indicating if the account was activated during computation.

COMPUTE_VM_STEPS.name: COMPUTE_VM_STEPS
COMPUTE_VM_STEPS.comment: Number of VM steps executed during computation.

COMPUTE_VM_INIT_STATE_HASH.name: COMPUTE_VM_INIT_STATE_HASH
COMPUTE_VM_INIT_STATE_HASH.comment: Hash of the VM's initial state during computation.

COMPUTE_VM_FINAL_STATE_HASH.name: COMPUTE_VM_FINAL_STATE_HASH
COMPUTE_VM_FINAL_STATE_HASH.comment: Hash of the VM's final state after computation.

SKIPPED_REASON.name: SKIPPED_REASON
SKIPPED_REASON.comment: Reason for skipping the transaction if it was skipped.

STORAGE_STATUS_CHANGE.name: STORAGE_STATUS_CHANGE
STORAGE_STATUS_CHANGE.comment: Storage status change during the transaction.

PREV_TRANS_LT.name: PREV_TRANS_LT
PREV_TRANS_LT.comment: Logical time of the previous transaction for the same account.

NOW.name: NOW
NOW.comment: Unix timestamp when the transaction was processed.

FACT_TRANSACTIONS_ID.name: FACT_TRANSACTIONS_ID
FACT_TRANSACTIONS_ID.comment: Unique identifier for the transaction record.

INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.comment: Timestamp when the record was inserted into the data warehouse.

metadata.name: DIM_LABELS
metadata.comment: The labels table is a store of one-to-one address identifiers, or an address name. Labels are broken out into a "type" (such as cex, dex, dapp, games, etc.) and a "subtype" (ex: contract_deployer, hot_wallet, token_contract, etc.) in order to help classify each address name into similar groups. Our labels are sourced from many different places, but can primarily be grouped into two categories: automatic and manual. Automatic labels are continuously labeled based on certain criteria, such as a known contract deploying another contract, behavior based algorithms for finding deposit wallets, and consistent data pulls of custom protocol APIs. Manual labels are done periodically to find addresses that cannot be found programmatically such as finding new protocol addresses, centralized exchange hot wallets, or trending addresses. Labels can also be added by our community by using our add-a-label tool (https://science.flipsidecrypto.xyz/add-a-label/) or on-chain with near (https://near.social/lord1.near/widget/Form) and are reviewed by our labels team. A label can be removed by our labels team if it is found to be incorrect or no longer relevant; this generally will only happen for mislabeled deposit wallets.

metadata.name: FACT_NFT_EVENTS
metadata.comment: Comprehensive data mart containing all NFT-related events including mints, transfers, sales, auctions, etc. Built on top of nft_items, nft_transfers, messages, and nft_sales tables.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: Timestamp of the block when the NFT event occurred, converted from timestamp.

TX_HASH.name: TX_HASH
TX_HASH.comment: Transaction hash associated with the NFT event, if applicable.

TYPE.name: TYPE
TYPE.comment: Type of NFT event: 'mint' (NFT deployment), 'put_on_sale' (NFT listed for sale), 'cancel_sale' (sale canceled), 'sale' (NFT sold), 'transfer' (direct NFT transfer), or 'bid' (auction bid).

SALE_TYPE.name: SALE_TYPE
SALE_TYPE.comment: Type of the sale: 'sale' for fixed price sales or 'auction' for auctions with bids.

NFT_ITEM_ADDRESS.name: NFT_ITEM_ADDRESS
NFT_ITEM_ADDRESS.comment: Address of the NFT item involved in the event.

NFT_ITEM_INDEX.name: NFT_ITEM_INDEX
NFT_ITEM_INDEX.comment: Index of the NFT item within its collection.

PAYMENT_ASSET.name: PAYMENT_ASSET
PAYMENT_ASSET.comment: Asset type used for payment. Currently only 'TON' is supported.

SALE_PRICE.name: SALE_PRICE
SALE_PRICE.comment: Price of the NFT in a sale event.

FORWARD_AMOUNT.name: FORWARD_AMOUNT
FORWARD_AMOUNT.comment: Amount of TON forwarded in transfer message, if related to the event.

ROYALTY_AMOUNT.name: ROYALTY_AMOUNT
ROYALTY_AMOUNT.comment: Amount of royalty in a sale event.

MARKETPLACE_FEE.name: MARKETPLACE_FEE
MARKETPLACE_FEE.comment: Fee charged by the marketplace in a sale event.

AUCTION_MAX_BID.name: AUCTION_MAX_BID
AUCTION_MAX_BID.comment: Maximum bid allowed in an auction.

AUCTION_MIN_BID.name: AUCTION_MIN_BID
AUCTION_MIN_BID.comment: Minimum bid required in an auction.

SALE_CONTRACT.name: SALE_CONTRACT
SALE_CONTRACT.comment: Address of the sale contract if related to the event.

MARKETPLACE_ADDRESS.name: MARKETPLACE_ADDRESS
MARKETPLACE_ADDRESS.comment: Address of the marketplace facilitating the sale.

OWNER_ADDRESS.name: OWNER_ADDRESS
OWNER_ADDRESS.comment: Current owner address of the NFT.

COLLECTION_ADDRESS.name: COLLECTION_ADDRESS
COLLECTION_ADDRESS.comment: Address of the NFT collection. May be null for standalone NFTs.

CONTENT_ONCHAIN.name: CONTENT_ONCHAIN
CONTENT_ONCHAIN.comment: NFT metadata extracted from on-chain data in JSON format.

TRACE_ID.name: TRACE_ID
TRACE_ID.comment: Trace ID for the transaction if applicable.

QUERY_ID.name: QUERY_ID
QUERY_ID.comment: Query ID associated with the event if it exists.

IS_INIT.name: IS_INIT
IS_INIT.comment: Boolean flag indicating if the NFT is initialized.

CUSTOM_PAYLOAD.name: CUSTOM_PAYLOAD
CUSTOM_PAYLOAD.comment: Custom payload from the transfer message if related to the event.

SALE_END_TIME.name: SALE_END_TIME
SALE_END_TIME.comment: End time of the sale if applicable.

FORWARD_PAYLOAD.name: FORWARD_PAYLOAD
FORWARD_PAYLOAD.comment: Payload of the forward message from transfer message if related to the event.

AUCTION_MIN_STEP.name: AUCTION_MIN_STEP
AUCTION_MIN_STEP.comment: Minimum step for bids in an auction.

PREV_OWNER.name: PREV_OWNER
PREV_OWNER.comment: Previous owner address. For mint events, this is the deployer address. For transfers, it's the previous owner. For sales, it's the seller. For bids, it's the bidder. Null for put_on_sale and cancel_sale events.

TIMESTAMP.comment: Unix timestamp of the NFT event.

LT.comment: Logical time of the NFT event.

FACT_NFT_EVENTS_ID.comment: Unique identifier for the NFT event record.

metadata.name: EZ_DECODED_EVENT_LOGS
metadata.comment:
'For information on how to submit a contract for decoding, as well as how ABIs are sourced, please visit [here](https://science.flipsidecrypto.xyz/abi-requestor/). This model contains decoded event logs for contracts that we have an ABI for. Please note, this table does not include all event logs, only those that we have an ABI for. The `decoded_log` column is the easiest place to query decoded data. It is a JSON object, where the keys are the names of the event parameters, and the values are the values of the event parameters. You can select from this column using the following sample format, `decoded_log:from::string` or more generally, `decoded_log:<event_param>::datatype`. See below for a full sample query. The `full_decoded_logs` column contains the same information, as well as additional fields such as the datatype of the decoded data. You may need to laterally flatten this column to query the data.
      
Sample query for USDC Transfer events:
```sql select  tx_hash, block_number, contract_address, decoded_log:from::string as from_address, decoded_log:to::string as to_address, decoded_log:value::integer as value from ethereum.core.fact_decoded_event_logs where contract_address = lower('0xA0b86991c6218b36c1d19D4a2e9Eb0cE3606eB48') and block_number between 16400000 and 16405000 and event_name = 'Transfer' limit 50```'
